    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-03-30T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-03-30T16:00:00-05:00" n="347"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d347">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">550.S1/623: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Atherton</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-03-30T16:00:00-05:00"
                            >March 30, 1933—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>60. For Davis from Phillips. As of possible interest to you, the British
                    Government has not yet replied to our memorandum, and while several
                    conversations have been held with Lindsay<note n="28" xml:id="d347fn28">Sir
                        Ronald Lindsay, British Ambassador.</note> during the past few days they
                    have been exploratory in scope.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
